FBIS3-24694 "drafr020_b_94002" FBIS-AFR-94-020 Document Type:Daily Report 31 Jan 1994 EAST AFRICA Djibouti Attend First Court Appearance AB3001204994 Paris AFP in English 1927 GMT 30 Jan 94 AB3001204994 Paris AFP Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Djibouti, Jan 30 (AFP)--Security was stepped up here Sunday [30 January] for the first court appearance of four opposition leaders accused of inciting an armed uprising. Police surrounded the court and held supporters of the outlawed United Front for Djibouti Opposition (FUOD) as the four party leaders were questioned by a judge. The four, Mohamed Ahmed Issa, Galal Abdourahman, Kamil Ali Mohamed, and Mahdi Ibrahim Goud, were detained in custody ahead of a decision on their trial. Legal proceedings were launched against the four after a petition calling for the armed fight in Djibouti to be stepped up was released during the second FUOD conference in Addis Ababa on January 23.
